# RBTV Config Source Rule

`.cursor/` at the repo root is an **installed copy** generated by `_config/install-rbtv.py`. NEVER create or edit files there directly.

## Canonical Locations

| What | Create/Edit in | Never in |
|------|---------------|----------|
| Rules (`bmad-rbtv-*.mdc`) | `_config/.cursor/rules/` | `.cursor/rules/` |
| Skills (`bmad-rbtv-*/SKILL.md`) | `_config/.cursor/skills/` | `.cursor/skills/` |
| Commands (`bmad-rbtv-*.md`) | `_config/.cursor/commands/` | `.cursor/commands/` |
| Agents (`bmad-rbtv-*.md`) | `_config/.cursor/agents/` | `.cursor/agents/` |
| MCP config (`mcp.json`) | `_config/.cursor/mcp.json` | `.cursor/mcp.json` |
| Admin-only rules (`admin-rbtv-*.mdc`) | `_admin/.cursor/rules/` | `.cursor/rules/` |

## Why

The installer copies `_config/.cursor/` → `{project-root}/.cursor/` during installation. Edits made directly in `.cursor/` are overwritten on next install and are not tracked by git (`.cursor/` is in `.gitignore`).

## After Editing

Re-run the installer to propagate changes to the installed copy:

```
python _config/install-rbtv.py --mode admin
```
